01:12:34,600 --> 01:12:36,660
This is the image, right?

2173
01:12:37,420 --> 01:12:38,580
What can be worse?

2174
01:12:39,120 --> 01:12:41,000
There's very few things that are worse than that.

2175
01:12:41,000 --> 01:12:57,160
But certainly the Holocaust, there are things that are worse than what I, what she, she showed me the reaction everyone should have to this or her reaction to this reality of the world that I was seeing with her at that moment and sort of stumbled upon.

2176
01:12:57,160 --> 01:13:09,820
So then when I went back in time, it became kind of a, then it became kind of a disappearance of time to put me in the right state of mind to do the, the exploration I needed to do at Mount Altos.

2177
01:13:09,820 --> 01:13:26,000
So the rest of the dream sequence that I outlined in, it's called the bizarre world of Odius Maximus in my book, because it's how bizarre I felt when I knew it was still me, but I'm going now into this, I have to adopt this cover of a character, so to speak, which is a CIA thing anyway.

2178
01:13:26,140 --> 01:13:30,380
So I should, but it was so, it was so unique, unusual and unique to me that it was really scary.

2179
01:13:30,520 --> 01:13:32,480
I wasn't sure I could not be that character.

2180
01:13:32,540 --> 01:13:34,160
I wasn't sure that it'd ever be Rolf again.

2181
01:13:34,160 --> 01:13:45,460
So then I'm going back in time as I'm traveling, as you would in those days to Athens and then from Athens to, and with every step I'm taking, the time is going back in time.

2182
01:13:46,400 --> 01:14:03,680
And, and by the time I get to Mount Altos at the capital city, which I had sort of landed in when I came off the boat in real life now and to where I'd had the dream a couple of days ago getting there, I saw that town again, but back in, back in the 1500s, you know, and I go there and I

2183
01:14:03,680 --> 01:14:14,180
present my credentials, so to speak at the capital to say, if you will, the governance people there, including this guy, Monk Gabriel, who was the head.

2184
01:14:15,020 --> 01:14:19,680
So Harry Hiller is this character that's in 19th century Paris-ish.

2185
01:14:19,880 --> 01:14:20,580
Paris, I leave him.

2186
01:14:20,580 --> 01:14:24,860
You leave him, he said, but he says, you are odious Maximus, you must go to Mount Athos.

2187
01:14:25,060 --> 01:14:31,440
You go to Mount Athos, and then all of a sudden you're like a few hundred years earlier in history.

2188
01:14:31,440 --> 01:14:33,520
So like 1400s, 1500s.

2189
01:14:33,520 --> 01:14:33,800
Correct.

2190
01:14:34,840 --> 01:14:36,120
Trapped up there, essentially.

2191
01:14:36,400 --> 01:14:37,140
Trapped up there.

2192
01:14:37,300 --> 01:14:44,820
Was there a gradient of time moving backwards from the 1800s to the 1400s or 1500s?

2193
01:14:44,880 --> 01:14:46,680
Or like all of a sudden you're in Mount Athos?

2194
01:14:47,060 --> 01:14:48,740
No, it was a gradient.

2195
01:14:49,060 --> 01:14:51,440
It was a, it was as if time was evaporating.

2196
01:14:52,260 --> 01:14:59,400
It was a way, like with each step, you could, like it got, that was what was so, I would say, very unnerving,

2197
01:14:59,400 --> 01:15:03,660
was going back in time, but feeling it happening as it's happening.

2198
01:15:04,040 --> 01:15:07,440
And it's getting, and I was trying to adjust, but it was getting too difficult to do.

2199
01:15:07,540 --> 01:15:13,140
So I tried to limit any contact with anybody, like on a ship or on a coach or as I'm going back,

2200
01:15:13,200 --> 01:15:19,160
because I didn't want anybody to say anything that would think I was some insane person and throw me in some.

2201
01:15:19,440 --> 01:15:24,140
You also don't want to alter the future forever with changing a variable or something.

2202
01:15:24,140 --> 01:15:26,340
I did not think that, but that's a good thought.

2203
01:15:26,500 --> 01:15:28,640
I did not think, I remember not thinking anything profound.

2204
01:15:28,760 --> 01:15:29,720
It was like pure survival.

2205
01:15:29,980 --> 01:15:34,260
I remember being in pure survival mode, including, I would say, my mind.

2206
01:15:34,420 --> 01:15:38,480
I was, I hoped I wasn't losing my mind to the point where, you know,

2207
01:15:38,560 --> 01:15:44,640
whatever the, say, inspiration was to adopt this way of thinking of myself

2208
01:15:44,640 --> 01:15:48,760
as being a very onerous, bad person, that I would overdo that again.

2209
01:15:48,760 --> 01:15:50,140
I mean, that wasn't really the point.

2210
01:15:50,220 --> 01:15:52,880
I kept reassuring myself, but I would have to play this out.

2211
01:15:53,020 --> 01:15:56,780
So I get up there and I describe this and long and short of it, the monks take me in,

2212
01:15:57,040 --> 01:15:58,440
even though they argued against it.

2213
01:15:58,460 --> 01:16:03,200
But this Gabriel, he saw something in me and he said, we're here to, like Peter said,

2214
01:16:03,420 --> 01:16:05,300
open our house to those who need it.

2215
01:16:05,380 --> 01:16:06,400
This, this man needs it.

2216
01:16:06,580 --> 01:16:10,060
So I get assigned to the monastery at Dona Dionisio,

2217
01:16:10,160 --> 01:16:12,420
which is where I happened to be when I was having the dream.

2218
01:16:12,820 --> 01:16:15,800
Do all, does all of this feel as real as this interview?

2219
01:16:16,140 --> 01:16:16,940
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

2220
01:16:16,940 --> 01:16:22,460
So it feels like any sort of real experience that you've had, it's indistinguishable.

2221
01:16:23,100 --> 01:16:23,800
Pretty much.

2222
01:16:24,000 --> 01:16:30,100
It's, there are things that occasionally in all the dreams, like the, the Sadat dream,

2223
01:16:30,100 --> 01:16:35,820
and I'd had other, you know, dreams also, which I lay out pretty much all of them

2224
01:16:35,820 --> 01:16:37,640
that I can remember in the book.

2225
01:16:37,920 --> 01:16:41,960
I had a dream of a basketball game dream, even like when I was a teenager.

2226
01:16:41,960 --> 01:16:47,840
And when I did, I knew immediately a qualitative reality in those dreams was close to reality,

2227
01:16:47,960 --> 01:16:51,780
but I could usually still understand it was a dream, if that makes sense.

2228
01:16:51,820 --> 01:16:53,580
So in this dream, I still knew I was in a dream.

2229
01:16:54,840 --> 01:16:59,960
And I could still distinguish the Rolf I was from the character going back in time.

2230
01:16:59,960 --> 01:17:06,040
So, but otherwise, outside of that, it seemed totally real to the point where I don't think

2231
01:17:06,040 --> 01:17:10,640
there were historical, like you've seen movies where there are things in, in movies that shouldn't

2232
01:17:10,640 --> 01:17:11,900
be there at a historical time.

2233
01:17:12,000 --> 01:17:15,740
You know, I didn't see telephones in the 16th century or things you shouldn't see, you know.

2234
01:17:16,360 --> 01:17:18,500
Were you wearing your clothing from?

2235
01:17:18,860 --> 01:17:19,540
And it changed.

2236
01:17:19,640 --> 01:17:20,620
It was changing.

2237
01:17:20,620 --> 01:17:22,280
It was going back time.

2238
01:17:22,280 --> 01:17:25,080
So your clothing was becoming more and more appropriate for the time.

2239
01:17:25,080 --> 01:17:30,700
Well, I also found myself, and I don't remember specifics on this, trying to find more appropriate

2240
01:17:30,700 --> 01:17:31,200
stuff.

2241
01:17:31,480 --> 01:17:35,560
So I wouldn't look like a space traveler back in the 17th century.

2242
01:17:35,700 --> 01:17:39,360
You know, I was trying to, like a person would do to try to fit in.

2243
01:17:39,420 --> 01:17:42,460
I was trying to alter my look and things like that.

2244
01:17:42,540 --> 01:17:44,220
I was getting a beard because I didn't shave.

2245
01:17:44,300 --> 01:17:45,880
You know, I remember those kinds of details.

2246
01:17:45,880 --> 01:17:50,980
So when I'm at the monastery, then it got deeper and deeper into what monks do, which

2247
01:17:50,980 --> 01:17:54,440
I learned a lot about through the dream, but also through what turned out to be two

2248
01:17:54,440 --> 01:17:57,980
trips there, spending a grand total of a month in Monathos.

2249
01:17:58,260 --> 01:18:03,540
That's the end, at the end of the story, that's what it consisted of because I got, of course,

2250
01:18:03,700 --> 01:18:08,500
very into this understanding, not just a dream, but then the encounter that followed, which

2251
01:18:08,500 --> 01:18:13,960
was the idea that you live a life in a monastery.

2252
01:18:13,960 --> 01:18:18,780
A lot of people just sort of quickly jump to the conclusion that's world evasion.

2253
01:18:19,300 --> 01:18:21,040
You just want to avoid the world.

2254
01:18:21,180 --> 01:18:22,080
You want to go off on yourself.

2255
01:18:22,180 --> 01:18:22,800
It's very selfish.

2256
01:18:23,000 --> 01:18:26,400
So I understand people when they say that about monastic lifestyles.

2257
01:18:26,500 --> 01:18:30,580
I don't feel that, in large measure, because I had this dream where I experienced it on

2258
01:18:30,580 --> 01:18:34,880
such an intense level, because for some people, it's the only way they can pursue God.

2259
01:18:34,980 --> 01:18:36,180
It's the only way they can be close to God.

2260
01:18:36,240 --> 01:18:37,940
It's the only way they can get themselves closer to God.

2261
01:18:38,180 --> 01:18:40,360
They don't give up on the world in most cases.

2262
01:18:41,140 --> 01:18:42,560
They're not doing it to avoid the world.

2263
01:18:42,560 --> 01:18:44,480
They're doing it to get close to God.

2264
01:18:44,940 --> 01:18:48,220
Sometimes there's a consequence of those other things when you do that.

2265
01:18:48,300 --> 01:18:49,120
So I felt that.

2266
01:18:49,500 --> 01:18:55,160
And so when I experienced the life up there, it was not experiences I had felt spiritually

2267
01:18:55,160 --> 01:18:59,160
before, which made, again, this was a new reality I was learning from.

2268
01:18:59,400 --> 01:19:05,620
It wasn't just adapting what I already knew and living it vicariously as a monk.

2269
01:19:05,660 --> 01:19:06,740
It was something very different.

2270
01:19:06,740 --> 01:19:10,260
Through the character I became in the monastery, I was growing.

2271
01:19:10,440 --> 01:19:11,020
I was developing.

2272
01:19:11,440 --> 01:19:12,880
I became a recluse up there.

2273
01:19:13,220 --> 01:19:14,220
You know, I learned to fly.

2274
01:19:14,720 --> 01:19:19,980
You know, and I remember, and I've talked to other people who have had the flying experience.

2275
01:19:20,440 --> 01:19:22,520
That's a different conversation we can have one day.

2276
01:19:22,520 --> 01:19:28,040
Because I've had reactions from people who read that part of my book and said, oh, I've done that.

2277
01:19:28,120 --> 01:19:29,360
I've been able to fly, you know.

2278
01:19:29,700 --> 01:19:31,800
For me, flying was a manifestation.

2279
01:19:32,340 --> 01:19:38,160
The more I think about it, I see it as a reward almost in a way.

2280
01:19:38,300 --> 01:19:44,520
A reward you're not asking for, but it's a tribute to opening your mind.

2281
01:19:44,520 --> 01:19:50,180
And when you're flying, you're spiritually open.

2282
01:19:50,780 --> 01:19:56,960
You're just in a different state of consciousness than you are when you're just praying, if that makes sense.

2283
01:19:57,780 --> 01:20:02,920
And what we talked about even right before the interview is what I didn't expect to find was,

2284
01:20:03,480 --> 01:20:07,800
as I went through the whole experience here, is the flying monk and I burned my hut up there,

2285
01:20:07,900 --> 01:20:09,480
like all the things a recluse does.

2286
01:20:09,940 --> 01:20:11,620
Were you doing, you were burning your hut there?

2287
01:20:11,620 --> 01:20:11,860
Yes.

2288
01:20:12,100 --> 01:20:12,420
Yes.

2289
01:20:12,420 --> 01:20:17,920
And so this is happening across months or weeks?

2290
01:20:18,340 --> 01:20:20,060
In the dream, it's months.

2291
01:20:20,220 --> 01:20:25,300
In reality, it's the course of the dream, which that's easy for me to do years in a dream.

2292
01:20:25,780 --> 01:20:30,500
But in my dream state, it was weeks, days went to weeks, went to months.

2293
01:20:30,500 --> 01:20:42,140
And so you are aware that your reality has drastically shifted from 20th century Rolf, CIA, case officer,

2294
01:20:42,420 --> 01:20:50,640
to, it was trying to catch the spy on Mount Athos, to, it's like you entered a portal and you are here for days upon days.

2295
01:20:50,640 --> 01:20:54,140
And you are going to sleep and waking up within this.

2296
01:20:54,140 --> 01:20:55,020
Yes, within the dream.

2297
01:20:55,680 --> 01:20:56,780
That is fascinating.

2298
01:20:56,780 --> 01:21:06,220
Well, the biggest thing about it was I knew at the time I had to dream, as I was dreaming, that I was dreaming and I might not be able to get back.

2299
01:21:06,220 --> 01:21:09,260
That was the scariest thing was I felt trapped.

2300
01:21:09,260 --> 01:21:11,480
And I wasn't sure I was going to wake up.

2301
01:21:11,480 --> 01:21:23,780
And at one point, I told one of the emissaries, so this Father Gabriel, who I got to kind of know, sent this other young monk called Evagrius, and he would come and meet me.

2302
01:21:23,900 --> 01:21:29,100
And I remember my encounters with him, and he was encouraging me, and we were talking all the time.

2303
01:21:29,160 --> 01:21:33,840
And I remember some of those, I just put snippets of them in the dream, and I frankly forgot some of them.

2304
01:21:33,840 --> 01:21:35,480
But I just knew that it was really alive.

2305
01:21:35,660 --> 01:21:40,840
It was my only contact with a human being when I was at a recluse stage, which was when I was doing the flying about.

2306
01:21:41,040 --> 01:21:44,040
And he told me, yeah, the other monks had seen me and wondered if it was real.

2307
01:21:44,200 --> 01:21:45,240
So I remember that stuff.

2308
01:21:45,280 --> 01:21:46,720
It was just so palpable.

2309
01:21:46,860 --> 01:21:49,000
But then I, of course, had three dreams within a dream.

2310
01:21:49,080 --> 01:21:53,680
And now we're reaching the culmination of the, as I would call, the fruition of the dream.

2311
01:21:53,860 --> 01:21:55,900
The point of the dream was what follows.

2312
01:21:55,900 --> 01:22:08,740
The farther I'm getting away from myself, the farther I'm detaching my faith in God from a selfish interest in me, that's when I start flying.

2313
01:22:08,820 --> 01:22:20,880
That's when I start, my spiritual growth is happening when I'm being less selfish, when I'm joining, sort of I call, the general universal salvation idea of mankind, if I'd call it that.

2314
01:22:20,880 --> 01:22:32,260
And the more intense my spiritual experiences were getting within my dream, to the point that I had three dreams within a dream, and very quickly, because one, and they're very intense.

2315
01:22:32,380 --> 01:22:41,280
One night I go to sleep in my dream, and I have a dream where I'm in the middle of a big room, and we all have to go pick numbers from what looks like a barbershop number thing.

2316
01:22:41,340 --> 01:22:43,680
You pull the number, and I got my number, two-digit number.

2317
01:22:43,980 --> 01:22:44,900
Oh, I don't remember the number.

2318
01:22:45,300 --> 01:22:45,720
It's too bad.

2319
01:22:45,800 --> 01:22:48,080
It would have been great to add to the number collection.

2320
01:22:48,080 --> 01:22:54,520
I was so frustrated I forgot the number, but it was a two-digit number, and everybody got a two-digit number.

2321
01:22:55,220 --> 01:22:56,360
I thought, well, this is very strange.

2322
01:22:56,420 --> 01:22:59,560
There are way more than 20 or 99 of us here.

2323
01:22:59,980 --> 01:23:02,100
What's the number?

2324
01:23:02,580 --> 01:23:03,780
Nobody explained anything.

2325
01:23:04,680 --> 01:23:05,480
Nobody talked.

2326
01:23:05,560 --> 01:23:07,880
It was just murmuring, walking around.

2327
01:23:08,680 --> 01:23:09,740
Then I woke up.

2328
01:23:09,940 --> 01:23:12,060
The barber shop clanged with the number.

2329
01:23:12,140 --> 01:23:13,020
I pulled the number up.

2330
01:23:13,320 --> 01:23:15,260
I woke up from the dream, and was in a dream.

2331
01:23:15,820 --> 01:23:16,780
It startled me.

2332
01:23:16,780 --> 01:23:22,460
So then in my dream, the next day, I go to sleep in my hut, and I have another dream.

2333
01:23:22,700 --> 01:23:23,320
It's the second dream.

2334
01:23:23,920 --> 01:23:26,680
Now in that dream, now I'm standing in the room again.

2335
01:23:26,740 --> 01:23:29,000
It's a big, round room with seven doors.

2336
01:23:31,400 --> 01:23:38,160
And I'm looking at my number, and I just had this wild thought, which I had never thought religiously, like until the dream.

2337
01:23:38,160 --> 01:23:40,280
And I thought, man, what a bummer.

2338
01:23:41,620 --> 01:23:46,660
I mean, we're all going to go through these doors, I guess, and these numbers must be, and we were wearing clothes.

2339
01:23:46,800 --> 01:23:48,060
They issued clothes.

2340
01:23:48,420 --> 01:23:51,480
And I had fine clothes, I remember, with brown suede shoes.

2341
01:23:51,620 --> 01:23:51,760
Yeah.

2342
01:23:51,760 --> 01:23:54,280
And some people were with rags.

2343
01:23:54,340 --> 01:24:02,860
And I saw an old woman in the corner, who, again, I thought, is this the Virgin Mary, the same woman I met in Paris?

2344
01:24:03,640 --> 01:24:04,780
I didn't know.

2345
01:24:05,020 --> 01:24:06,640
So I don't want to overstate it.

2346
01:24:07,140 --> 01:24:08,260
But I thought, is that her?

2347
01:24:08,940 --> 01:24:10,780
And I said, well, I don't know.

2348
01:24:10,820 --> 01:24:11,300
We'll see what happened.

2349
01:24:11,360 --> 01:24:14,060
I kept my eye on her, but I didn't want to go up to anybody or say anything.

2350
01:24:14,140 --> 01:24:16,860
It was like, everything in this, I was just like trying to survive.

2351
01:24:17,220 --> 01:24:19,340
It was really, I was trying to survive, even in my dream within a dream.

2352
01:24:19,940 --> 01:24:21,280
And then the doors opened.

2353
01:24:22,240 --> 01:24:24,500
Seven doors opened, and we had to walk through the doors.

2354
01:24:24,500 --> 01:24:28,680
And I remember thinking the heretical thought, like in a way of doubting God again.

2355
01:24:29,360 --> 01:24:33,960
What if my number's like right under the ones that are going to heaven, I'm going to hell?

2356
01:24:35,220 --> 01:24:36,840
I mean, imagine missing by one number.

2357
01:24:37,540 --> 01:24:38,800
But it's kind of a stupid thought.

2358
01:24:38,800 --> 01:24:42,300
Like, if the situation were real, that's a real thing.

2359
01:24:42,680 --> 01:24:44,920
If there's such a thing as heaven and hell, right?

2360
01:24:45,160 --> 01:24:50,960
Which I've never believed after this and other things, that there's such a literal thing as that.

2361
01:24:51,080 --> 01:24:52,660
I think heaven and hell is in your mind.

2362
01:24:53,680 --> 01:24:55,100
But partially because of this.

2363
01:24:55,480 --> 01:24:58,120
So then, boom, wake up again, startled by this.

2364
01:24:58,320 --> 01:25:00,580
The doors groaning and having to walk through them.

2365
01:25:00,840 --> 01:25:02,860
And then the third dream is walking through the door.

2366
01:25:03,640 --> 01:25:07,600
And I remember it very carefully, particularly when I reread it, you know,

2367
01:25:07,600 --> 01:25:12,140
last night, actually, where I'm standing at the beach.

2368
01:25:12,160 --> 01:25:14,360
And it brought it all back to me really clearly.

2369
01:25:14,520 --> 01:25:16,040
It was a dark, dark night.

2370
01:25:16,120 --> 01:25:17,180
Not a star in the sky.

2371
01:25:17,240 --> 01:25:17,800
I remember that.

2372
01:25:18,400 --> 01:25:20,920
But the sun, it was bright light.

2373
01:25:21,020 --> 01:25:22,240
I thought, well, the sun's not up.

2374
01:25:22,260 --> 01:25:24,840
But it was a bright light on the other side of the...

2375
01:25:24,840 --> 01:25:27,900
And I remember thinking of the contradiction that the sun's not out.

2376
01:25:27,980 --> 01:25:28,660
What's that light?

2377
01:25:28,660 --> 01:25:29,460
It wasn't the moon.

2378
01:25:29,960 --> 01:25:32,380
There's something very bright on the other side of the shore.

2379
01:25:32,720 --> 01:25:35,900
And it was like a river kind of thing.

2380
01:25:36,100 --> 01:25:37,780
A river, like a wide river.

2381
01:25:38,460 --> 01:25:40,260
And it was turning dark.

2382
01:25:40,820 --> 01:25:43,600
And I could tell, well, we were all being encouraged.

2383
01:25:43,900 --> 01:25:44,380
We knew.

2384
01:25:44,380 --> 01:25:45,380
No one was saying anything.

2385
01:25:45,460 --> 01:25:49,600
And now I'm saying, you had to walk across the river to the other side.

2386
01:25:50,340 --> 01:25:53,560
Which I took, at that time, I thought, this must be salvation.

2387
01:25:53,760 --> 01:25:56,200
The test of salvation for all of us.

2388
01:25:57,140 --> 01:26:01,160
And I'm walking on the top of the water, like Christ, you know, in Galilee, you know.

2389
01:26:01,360 --> 01:26:04,540
And I'm thinking, oh, this can't hold me with my brown suede shoes.

2390
01:26:05,520 --> 01:26:08,820
And I, but it started to work.

2391
01:26:08,820 --> 01:26:15,640
And I said, well, if I put all my effort into my faith, maybe I'll make it to the other side.

2392
01:26:16,340 --> 01:26:18,160
And then people are, I heard plunk.

2393
01:26:18,280 --> 01:26:22,780
It was a terrible sound, like somebody going into the water and being swept away in the depths.

2394
01:26:22,900 --> 01:26:25,820
And you couldn't see below, except like an inch below your shoes.

2395
01:26:26,780 --> 01:26:29,320
And I was wondering if I stupidly think of my shoes are getting wet.

2396
01:26:30,080 --> 01:26:30,940
I remember thinking that.

2397
01:26:31,000 --> 01:26:32,640
I was like, oh, these shoes are going to get ruined.

2398
01:26:32,700 --> 01:26:33,340
They're going to be stained.

2399
01:26:34,300 --> 01:26:35,320
I really did.

2400
01:26:35,320 --> 01:26:40,880
And then, you know, sure enough, I get halfway across and think, I can do this.

2401
01:26:40,920 --> 01:26:41,560
I can make this.

2402
01:26:41,600 --> 01:26:43,120
And then the old woman's right next to me.

2403
01:26:43,480 --> 01:26:45,660
And she stumbles and loses her step.

2404
01:26:45,700 --> 01:26:48,780
And I instinctively just tried to grab her arm to hold her up.

2405
01:26:48,840 --> 01:26:50,660
And we both went swept away and I woke up.

2406
01:26:51,000 --> 01:26:51,540
The Virgin Mary.

2407
01:26:52,200 --> 01:26:53,040
Well, I don't.

2408
01:26:53,180 --> 01:26:54,800
What you interpret to be the Virgin.

2409
01:26:54,840 --> 01:26:55,140
What I interpret, probably.

2410
01:26:55,440 --> 01:27:01,220
Because it tied into the, but then the final scene is that I wake up.

2411
01:27:01,600 --> 01:27:03,540
Like this is the, I'm done with the dream.

2412
01:27:03,540 --> 01:27:07,140
That was, getting swept away was the final part of the dream.

2413
01:27:07,220 --> 01:27:14,640
So I wake up at the throne sitting there and I realized I saw a light in the church.

2414
01:27:14,740 --> 01:27:22,160
This was like this from distance, maybe we're going to say six, seven yards or whatever it is, 15 feet to your windows over there, right?

2415
01:27:22,360 --> 01:27:27,460
That's where the wall of the church was with the windows, stained glass kind of windows I had.

2416
01:27:27,460 --> 01:27:32,600
And I saw this red light moving along the thing.

2417
01:27:32,680 --> 01:27:41,380
And I got up out of the chair and moved toward the window and it had gone all the way up to the front, you know, of the church, the altar.

2418
01:27:41,980 --> 01:27:45,180
And was sitting there burning, you know, red.

2419
01:27:45,180 --> 01:27:54,480
And now I think, but the lights were related, the light and the red light, of course, of the model and the red light of Mary.

2420
01:27:54,760 --> 01:27:58,460
So I attached all the Marys together in the dream.

2421
01:27:58,600 --> 01:27:59,420
This must be this.

2422
01:27:59,500 --> 01:28:03,540
But to be clear, I had never seen the Virgin Mary.

2423
01:28:03,540 --> 01:28:08,260
So I saw the dream image of her and then I saw the light, which I took to be.

2424
01:28:08,380 --> 01:28:10,060
I took that light immediately when I saw it.

2425
01:28:10,280 --> 01:28:11,920
I talked to a monk the next day.

2426
01:28:12,420 --> 01:28:17,760
I said, I saw this mysterious light in the church after it was closed and it moved from here to here.

2427
01:28:18,040 --> 01:28:20,840
I thought he would just say, oh, are you dreaming something?

2428
01:28:20,980 --> 01:28:22,780
I said, well, I was awake, I said.

2429
01:28:22,860 --> 01:28:24,420
But he said, no, he said this.

2430
01:28:24,480 --> 01:28:26,380
It was like his name was Monk Timotheus.

2431
01:28:26,500 --> 01:28:28,600
And I ended up going back to him.

2432
01:28:28,700 --> 01:28:29,560
I'll seek him out.

2433
01:28:29,560 --> 01:28:40,840
And he ended up taking me back to his cell that they call it where they live, their little like bunk in a stone place, really, really austere, you know, rugged kind of living conditions.

2434
01:28:41,240 --> 01:28:43,180
And he had like 10 books on his shelf.

2435
01:28:43,280 --> 01:28:49,600
He gave me three of them about Athos because he said, I just want you to read more about this because this seemed like you saw that for a reason.

2436
01:28:49,740 --> 01:28:56,560
He goes, there are monks who have said they've seen this is the light of the Virgin Mary going down the thing.

2437
01:28:56,680 --> 01:28:58,280
And it seems like you might have seen that.

2438
01:28:58,340 --> 01:28:59,220
I don't understand it.

2439
01:28:59,220 --> 01:29:03,980
He was very confused by it because he said, you're not even, he even tested me and said, you're not even Orthodox, are you?

2440
01:29:03,980 --> 01:29:04,620
He said, no, no.

2441
01:29:04,680 --> 01:29:05,280
He went through that.

2442
01:29:05,340 --> 01:29:07,340
He said, well, I don't know, but I'm not going to doubt it.

2443
01:29:07,460 --> 01:29:10,820
And that's when he gave me, and I kept those books for, I still have those books.

2444
01:29:10,960 --> 01:29:16,960
When you wake up and you're at the church and you see the red light and maybe that's somewhat symbolic of the Virgin Mary.

2445
01:29:17,040 --> 01:29:17,380
Yeah, yeah.

2446
01:29:17,920 --> 01:29:21,780
Is that in 19, is that 1990s or is that?

2447
01:29:21,780 --> 01:29:24,240
Yes, that's 1991.

2448
01:29:24,240 --> 01:29:24,920
Okay.

2449
01:29:25,360 --> 01:29:32,000
So you basically, you go back to 1800s Paris, then you go to Mount Athos.

2450
01:29:32,120 --> 01:29:34,800
Mount Athos is days turned into months.

2451
01:29:35,400 --> 01:29:43,500
You are odious Maximus, this monk who goes through all these kind of ascetic protocols and you're fasting.

2452
01:29:43,500 --> 01:29:46,820
And you say you're burning your huts and stuff?

2453
01:29:46,820 --> 01:29:52,680
Well, then I finally requested permission to go away from the monastery and just be a recluse in the wild, in the wilderness.

2454
01:29:53,000 --> 01:29:55,180
You know, like there's a tradition there.

2455
01:29:55,300 --> 01:29:59,780
Some monks go out and they just separate themselves from everybody, even their fellow monks.

2456
01:29:59,780 --> 01:30:05,840
And the only time they see anybody is they come in to get provisions or medical emergency or something.

2457
01:30:05,980 --> 01:30:10,460
I mean, they don't completely abandon all ties to civilization.

2458
01:30:10,760 --> 01:30:15,520
If you call that civilization, they just limit it as much as possible to get even closer and closer.

2459
01:30:15,520 --> 01:30:30,060
And, uh, in fact, I ended up meeting a recluse who I feel was like kind of a full circle experience that I actually met a real recluse the second time I went to Mount Athos and, uh, who gave me a book and tremendous conversation we had about the apocalypse.

2460
01:30:30,560 --> 01:30:35,820
I mean, here, normally people get together, I'm sitting on a curb, you know, with this guy and talking about things.

2461
01:30:35,860 --> 01:30:39,720
And he's asking me who I was and where I worked and I have a family back in this day.

2462
01:30:39,800 --> 01:30:41,920
And he said, I haven't seen anybody in a few weeks.

2463
01:30:41,980 --> 01:30:42,660
This is kind of nice.

2464
01:30:42,660 --> 01:30:48,220
He was carrying bags of, um, he's carrying some, some lettuce and one bag, plastic bag.

2465
01:30:48,260 --> 01:30:52,240
And the other bag, he's carrying a baguette, you know, he's going back to the wild, into the woods.

2466
01:30:52,400 --> 01:30:55,020
But anyway, he stopped and chatted me up.

2467
01:30:55,040 --> 01:31:00,060
And the next thing you know, we're talking for a couple hours on, turned out into the apocalypse and everything else.

2468
01:31:00,080 --> 01:31:00,600
And it was amazing.

2469
01:31:00,640 --> 01:31:04,600
Like we both had studied the same books about this, but that's, that's the side.

2470
01:31:04,660 --> 01:31:07,560
That's just the idea of what it meant when I went into this room.

2471
01:31:07,560 --> 01:31:15,120
It was almost like I needed this full circle, which is so much of the story for me, where things are explained later.

2472
01:31:15,120 --> 01:31:21,160
So when I, at the time I saw the light of the Virgin Mary, I mean, I honestly didn't think that much of it.

2473
01:31:21,720 --> 01:31:22,520
It was a light.

2474
01:31:22,580 --> 01:31:23,260
Maybe it was a light.

2475
01:31:23,360 --> 01:31:26,440
Even the image of the old woman, maybe it was her, maybe it was not her.

2476
01:31:27,060 --> 01:31:31,020
So I had all those things, you know, the dream itself is the way you describe.

2477
01:31:31,100 --> 01:31:34,640
And that has its own, it's its own story in a way.

2478
01:31:34,640 --> 01:31:40,520
But it wasn't until two more things that happened with the Virgin Mary that it all came together.

2479
01:31:41,960 --> 01:31:43,400
It's fascinating.

2480
01:31:43,680 --> 01:31:51,700
And you also then come to realize that there had been Virgin Mary apparitions all over Mount Athos?

2481
01:31:51,700 --> 01:31:52,560
Not at this point.

2482
01:31:52,700 --> 01:31:52,940
Okay.

2483
01:31:53,040 --> 01:31:54,240
That was, but later you were.

2484
01:31:54,240 --> 01:32:12,620
I had talked to people there later, everything was later, including the story of the Virgin Mary being on the mountain that I'd learned and wasn't until 2006 or seven, 2007, that I heard some of the backstory of the history and lore that included the site.

2485
01:32:12,620 --> 01:32:22,240
So I'll save that because at this point, I don't know any of this, including, I wasn't ready at that point, prepared in the sense of thinking it would happen to me.

2486
01:32:22,320 --> 01:32:31,000
So there was no predisposition, for example, to actually meet the Virgin Mary or understand what, you know, like what has happened historically with the Virgin Mary.

2487
01:32:31,100 --> 01:32:39,020
Some people ask me that, well, when you started to have your Virgin Mary experiences, were they in any way because you read about, you know, Lords or Fatima and all this?

2488
01:32:39,020 --> 01:32:42,780
I said, well, I honestly knew nothing about any of that at this point.

2489
01:32:43,500 --> 01:32:44,780
And this was 1991.

2490
01:32:45,460 --> 01:32:52,140
What did you find out later in 2006 and seven about the Virgin Mary showing up at Mount Athos?

2491
01:32:52,140 --> 01:33:02,340
Because I think it's very fascinating that there's some historical corroboration on other people are experiencing what you're experiencing spiritually in this specific location.

2492
01:33:02,340 --> 01:33:21,540
Well, I find out that there's at least a legend lore that they have at Mount Athos that the Virgin Mary, after Christ was crucified and rose from the dead, was traveling along with other Christians at the time, or apostles, around in ships.

2493
01:33:21,540 --> 01:33:24,980
And, of course, they were all based in Corinth and places like that.

2494
01:33:25,280 --> 01:33:45,540
So she was on a ship on its way to sea of all things, John at Patmos, and also to go to Cyprus because Lazarus supposedly fled Israel when the Romans started looking for him because they wanted to execute him as being this person who rose from the dead.

2495
01:33:45,540 --> 01:33:50,440
It was a very disruptive idea that Jesus was going around raising people from the dead, right?

2496
01:33:50,780 --> 01:34:04,920
It was the reason why both the Jews and the Romans saw the early Christians, they called the way at that point, they weren't called Christians, as being saboteurs, disruptive to order and society.

2497
01:34:05,100 --> 01:34:06,600
So they were hunting him down, actually.

2498
01:34:06,600 --> 01:34:07,740
So he fled, apparently.

2499
01:34:08,140 --> 01:34:12,720
And I didn't believe that story either until, I believe, I didn't like, maybe it's true, maybe it's not.

2500
01:34:13,140 --> 01:34:29,480
And there's actually, if anybody listeners goes to Nicosia, Cyprus, I urge you to take a look at the Lazarus's tomb, which is supposedly in Cyprus, where he went and became the first bishop, starting the church in there.

2501
01:34:29,480 --> 01:34:42,480
So Mary was supposedly traveling on a ship, and there was a big storm, which that part of the Aegean is famous for that, going all the way back to the Spartans and the Athens, having a huge summer storm that ruined fleets and everything, shipwrecked fleets.

2502
01:34:42,480 --> 01:35:00,240
And she got blown on the island of Monathos, and there's a monastery placed on the site where she supposedly landed, went ashore, called Evaron, on the, it's on the west coast of this peninsula, at that monastery, in the south part of the monastery.

2503
01:35:00,240 --> 01:35:14,960
And I've been to that monastery, but it wasn't until this 2005, 2006 period, when a monk told me the whole story about this little icon in a hut right on the shore, that this hut, this is supposedly the spot where she landed at that time.

2504
01:35:15,140 --> 01:35:15,280
Wow.

2505
01:35:15,700 --> 01:35:17,540
Wow, this has got way more.

2506
01:35:18,020 --> 01:35:28,660
And of course, I've sent my book and gotten letters back from the Vatican and also from the Orthodox Church hierarchy in Istanbul, Turkey.

2507
01:35:28,660 --> 01:35:32,400
And the letter I got from the Orthodox Church was really priceless.

2508
01:35:32,580 --> 01:35:44,980
It said, basically, you know, we wish you had become one of us and still joined the Catholics, but we still consider you, you know, a friend of ours, and your book is in our library, and his eminence is Reddit and all that.

2509
01:35:45,080 --> 01:35:53,000
Because I really appreciated that, because I've said to many people, the accident of me being Catholic or Orthodox is not what any of this is about.

2510
01:35:53,940 --> 01:35:54,380
Right?

2511
01:35:54,480 --> 01:35:55,760
And I think they appreciated that.

2512
01:35:55,760 --> 01:35:59,420
And Mary belongs to the world, not to Catholics or Orthodox.

2513
01:36:00,140 --> 01:36:21,760
Orthodox, in Monathos, they consider her the whole object of the veneration that the mountain is dedicated to, which is why women to this day can't go—and I think this is misguided, just to put that out there—but women to this day cannot go on Monathos, step foot on Monathos, because it's dedicated completely to Mary at the exclusion of all women.

2514
01:36:21,760 --> 01:36:25,420
As I said, I think this is veneration that goes too far.

2515
01:36:25,420 --> 01:36:35,420
But the point of it is to emphasize how fundamental Mary's history and role is—

2516
01:36:35,960 --> 01:36:44,460
Have other visitors or pilgrims experienced Mary that explicitly, just like you there at Monathos, specifically?

2517
01:36:44,460 --> 01:37:00,660
Yes, yes. And I can't enumerate their examples, but I know it's not a unique phenomenon. So much so that I would say, like I'm having with you, Jesse, this is highly unusual to have an easy conversation on these subjects, right?

2518
01:37:00,660 --> 01:37:21,540
You can do that. Most people can't. What's been very gratifying is that I never bring it up, the subjects, any of these subjects almost, except the just, you know, obviously the intelligence and all history and all that I do, but any of the religious or focus on God with anybody who doesn't bring it up.

2519
01:37:21,540 --> 01:37:30,340
And then I usually bring it up, and I found some very fascinating takes or additions that people have to make on what I've said that they've experienced.

2520
01:37:30,480 --> 01:37:40,860
Like a really close friend of mine, I would never have expected this, came to me especially to say he's had very vivid dreams of flying after reading about that part of my book.

2521
01:37:40,860 --> 01:37:52,680
And it's very gratifying to hear. I've also had more basic things of people saying, you know, why would you join a church with all this that you describe yourself in your book as having all this sex abuse and this and that?

2522
01:37:52,700 --> 01:37:57,000
And I said, well, I said, I never give up on the church like I never give up on your faith.

2523
01:37:57,120 --> 01:38:05,160
But those kinds of conversations have been the great gifts of writing the book.

2524
01:38:05,160 --> 01:38:12,300
So while you're at Mount Athos and you're this character, Odios Maximus, what do you feel like it is?

2525
01:38:12,300 --> 01:38:20,180
So you feel like it's your mission to get closer to God by sort of detaching yourself from the contemporary world in some ways?

2526
01:38:20,380 --> 01:38:23,160
And so what are you doing on a day-to-day basis?

2527
01:38:23,440 --> 01:38:28,300
You're fasting and you're praying or what's your day-to-day life like?

2528
01:38:28,300 --> 01:38:36,280
And again, this feels as real as you waking up, you know, in, you know, Maryland where you live, right?

2529
01:38:36,500 --> 01:38:42,620
Yeah, well, I remember feeling a bit of a contradiction of feelings.

2530
01:38:43,120 --> 01:38:51,300
On the one hand, being there and doing things like tending to the grapes and cleaning the dishes, you know, until I become a recluse.

2531
01:38:51,300 --> 01:38:58,060
But then it's just trying to survive in the wild and, you know, that kind of thing, doing like continual prayer or that kind of thing.

2532
01:38:58,520 --> 01:39:02,120
But up until that point, I'm thinking, I mean, I'm also miserable.

2533
01:39:02,200 --> 01:39:02,960
I want to go home.

2534
01:39:04,100 --> 01:39:06,440
So I never lost the feeling I wanted out.

2535
01:39:07,720 --> 01:39:08,740
Do you feel stuck?

2536
01:39:08,940 --> 01:39:09,740
I felt stuck.

2537
01:39:09,840 --> 01:39:11,240
Yeah, I said that a few times.

2538
01:39:11,240 --> 01:39:13,780
But I felt very stuck when I was in the recluse phase.

2539
01:39:13,780 --> 01:39:22,780
But I understood without any, like, there was no messaging or voicing or, which I've never heard, by the way, with mystical experiences, any like audio.

2540
01:39:23,180 --> 01:39:26,980
It's interesting, real audio, real talking words.

2541
01:39:27,220 --> 01:39:32,220
But it was the idea that I needed to do this to go home.

2542
01:39:32,540 --> 01:39:37,420
I needed to go through these different levels of this experience and the dream before I could.

2543
01:39:38,180 --> 01:39:38,960
No one said that.

2544
01:39:39,720 --> 01:39:40,880
But I knew it.

2545
01:39:40,880 --> 01:39:46,260
I knew that until I had gone through the different levels of what was expected, I couldn't go.

2546
01:39:46,320 --> 01:39:47,980
It was almost like it was a spiritual training.

2547
01:39:48,100 --> 01:39:52,220
I mean, the Jesuits call it their spiritual exercises that they go through.

2548
01:39:52,340 --> 01:39:54,080
This was much more intense than the dream.

2549
01:39:54,440 --> 01:39:59,560
How old were you as Rolf when you went back, when you time-traveled as Odeus Maximus?

2550
01:40:00,160 --> 01:40:00,780
How old were you?

2551
01:40:00,860 --> 01:40:01,600
In my real life?

2552
01:40:01,660 --> 01:40:02,320
Yeah, in your real life.

2553
01:40:02,320 --> 01:40:06,560
So it's 1991, and I'm born in 54.

2554
01:40:07,740 --> 01:40:09,380
So it's, what, 40?

2555
01:40:09,660 --> 01:40:10,460
Yeah, 37.

2556
01:40:10,460 --> 01:40:10,980
Interesting.

2557
01:40:11,520 --> 01:40:11,780
Yeah.

2558
01:40:12,480 --> 01:40:17,780
And so you're communing with Gabriel and the other monks as well.

2559
01:40:17,900 --> 01:40:17,980
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

2560
01:40:18,400 --> 01:40:21,960
Did you ever tell them, hey, like, I'm kind of trapped here.

2561
01:40:22,180 --> 01:40:23,260
Oh, I, the only, yeah, no.

2562
01:40:23,400 --> 01:40:24,740
I actually exist in the future.

2563
01:40:24,880 --> 01:40:25,440
No, no.

2564
01:40:25,520 --> 01:40:26,520
It was like a cover.

2565
01:40:26,840 --> 01:40:27,920
I was living my cover.

2566
01:40:27,920 --> 01:40:39,620
Until, at the very end, near the end, after, you know, in one of the times I wore the brown suede shoes in my dream within a dream, and then they were suddenly under my hut.

2567
01:40:39,620 --> 01:40:40,660
So they're in the dream now.

2568
01:40:40,660 --> 01:40:49,140
They had gone from the dream within the dream to somehow peering in my dream, and that was very discombobulating, right?

2569
01:40:49,140 --> 01:40:58,680
And at that point, when Evagrius came back on another, to check on me, make sure I hadn't plunged off a cliff or something, I told him.

2570
01:40:58,680 --> 01:41:03,300
And I told him who I really was, and I remember the reaction.

2571
01:41:03,720 --> 01:41:11,200
I had to, by the way, I never knew exactly all, some of the things I said, but I knew that all of it was consistent.

2572
01:41:11,320 --> 01:41:19,060
So when I had to create dialogue with Evagrius on this scene in my book that I don't remember exactly what the dialogue was.

2573
01:41:19,060 --> 01:41:20,720
As with waking memory.

2574
01:41:20,780 --> 01:41:20,980
Right.

2575
01:41:21,100 --> 01:41:22,320
So I did with my best.

2576
01:41:22,320 --> 01:41:27,680
So I don't want anybody out there to think I've got this photographic memory or anything, but it's very close.

2577
01:41:27,680 --> 01:41:29,200
So what did you roughly say?

2578
01:41:29,200 --> 01:41:39,920
The main thing I remember that I based the dialogue I created on was, and to be true to that, was the idea that Evagrius was wise beyond his years.

2579
01:41:39,980 --> 01:41:43,680
He was a young, spry little monk, wise beyond his years.

2580
01:41:44,540 --> 01:41:53,840
And when I told him the reality, I did it because I knew he was wise, and I needed somebody to tell, and it was him.

2581
01:41:53,940 --> 01:41:55,480
He was a someone I could trust.

2582
01:41:55,480 --> 01:42:13,880
And he reacted in a way that redeemed my idea that this was a good time to do it by basically reacting as I would have hoped, which is, I hope you get back to your family and keep praying to God and God will take care of you.

2583
01:42:13,880 --> 01:42:30,660
And in a way that I suddenly felt a sense of peace, knowing this wasn't going to go without somebody knowing what had happened to me, and maybe I will get back, because I think this guy would offer me some wisdom and insight into that, and he did.

2584
01:42:30,660 --> 01:42:34,320
Did he freak out at all and say, what, you exist in the future?

2585
01:42:34,740 --> 01:42:35,800
No, no, no.

2586
01:42:35,920 --> 01:42:45,140
Did you say, there's this place, it's called America, or the United States, and it ends up breaking off from England in 1776?

2587
01:42:45,240 --> 01:42:46,840
Did you have to go through any of that?

2588
01:42:46,840 --> 01:42:52,180
Or he just kind of took it on its more spiritual dimension or something and kind of ran with it?

2589
01:42:52,180 --> 01:42:53,560
Well, Jesse, there was one thing.

2590
01:42:53,620 --> 01:43:01,600
No, I didn't do any of that, but I made a big slip up early on that I realized, and nobody called me on it.

2591
01:43:01,620 --> 01:43:03,560
I think they knew there was something really wrong.

2592
01:43:03,560 --> 01:43:12,400
Going back to my presentation of my credentials, so to speak, to Gabriel, when I said I was Odeus Maximus and all this stuff, I'm not who I was.

2593
01:43:13,100 --> 01:43:28,080
But I did say something really absurd, where I said, you know, I'm an American mystic, because I knew I had to present myself as a mystic, because I wouldn't be able to go through any grilling on doctrine or theology or stuff they might expect.

2594
01:43:28,080 --> 01:43:40,680
So I had to play the mystic card, and then you maybe don't, or you can grunt, or I was going to fake it in a way that I knew I couldn't if I had to actually explain my knowledge of liturgy or anything else.

2595
01:43:40,800 --> 01:43:44,000
And they saw through it, and he did, but he had pity, right?

2596
01:43:44,040 --> 01:43:46,040
That was the earlier description.

2597
01:43:46,180 --> 01:43:51,020
But I said at the time, I'm an American mystic, thinking I came from this continent, that didn't exist, right?

2598
01:43:51,040 --> 01:43:53,380
At least in their minds, nobody said anything.

2599
01:43:53,380 --> 01:44:03,880
And so when I presented the story at the end, my real name and future, I'm from the future, to this monk, he seemed to take it all in stride.

2600
01:44:04,600 --> 01:44:23,320
And it's really interesting, because if there are people, I think, who understand the notion of future time travel, there's no super religious, no, super spiritual person, at least in the Christianity, I think all of them.

2601
01:44:23,380 --> 01:44:35,900
Honestly, and the monotheistic religions, who aren't able to separate time from discussion in a way where they're comfortable with the idea of past, future.

2602
01:44:36,140 --> 01:44:46,880
Because for one thing, the most credible witnesses to what's going to come and what the past means are the prophets, right?

2603
01:44:46,880 --> 01:44:54,680
It's Ezekiel, Daniel, Revelations, John, it's Christ, who talked about the raising of Jerusalem.

2604
01:44:54,980 --> 01:45:04,680
It's the history of the church is in question when people—in fact, even Christ himself said he can't predict when the future ends, or that's up to God.

2605
01:45:04,680 --> 01:45:18,680
So there are limits, and I don't look at prophets as soothsayers in the, you know, sort of Shakespearean tradition of Ides of March, or—no, prophets are those who concede into the future what happens.

2606
01:45:18,780 --> 01:45:22,480
They don't influence it, if that makes sense.

2607
01:45:22,480 --> 01:45:36,540
Do you think, right now, as we speak, Rolf is also Odius Maximus, living in 15th century Mount Athos, Greece, trying to, you know, commune with God?

2608
01:45:36,540 --> 01:45:39,760
And, oh, wow, that's those—see, now we're getting into fun stuff.

2609
01:45:40,080 --> 01:45:42,980
But, I mean, everything I've said is a product of—

2610
01:45:42,980 --> 01:45:44,380
You could speculate, you know?

2611
01:45:44,380 --> 01:45:54,000
And I will, and I'll just say as a preface that everything I say on this subject is not—is really philosophical science.

2612
01:45:54,520 --> 01:45:59,640
It's drawn from my greatest love intellectually in the world, which is philosophy, which is what?

2613
01:45:59,960 --> 01:46:01,460
The love of wisdom, right?

2614
01:46:01,480 --> 01:46:02,180
The love of knowledge.

2615
01:46:02,180 --> 01:46:08,620
And so, in that spirit, I think that it's possible.

2616
01:46:09,140 --> 01:46:18,360
And my experiences bear this out for me, that the dreams we create are as real as the physical reality we're in, which means the answer to your question would be yes.

2617
01:46:19,080 --> 01:46:21,820
Because if I dreamt it, and I created it—

2618
01:46:21,820 --> 01:46:23,360
And it felt real.

2619
01:46:23,440 --> 01:46:24,060
It didn't feel—

2620
01:46:24,060 --> 01:46:25,260
And it felt real, and I created it.

2621
01:46:25,260 --> 01:46:42,840
Now, the more you get into whether you're taking a trip, so to speak, in reality versus—like, I make this great distinction, which I'm not sure is as great a distinction in as bright lines as I make it, between when I met the Virgin Mary and when I've had interactions.

2622
01:46:42,840 --> 01:46:49,800
Just like when you pray to God and you think you're getting responses and telling—versus actually, like, meeting God.

2623
01:46:50,080 --> 01:46:50,300
Yeah.

2624
01:46:50,360 --> 01:46:50,720
Yeah, yeah.

2625
01:46:50,840 --> 01:46:54,520
But let's go a little deeper into this Odius Maximus example.

2626
01:46:54,760 --> 01:46:57,620
Do you think that that is a real historical figure?

2627
01:46:58,540 --> 01:46:59,300
Yeah, I know he is.

2628
01:46:59,400 --> 01:47:00,700
That was one of the ironies.

2629
01:47:00,700 --> 01:47:04,120
So, to my great shock—great shock.

2630
01:47:04,200 --> 01:47:05,780
This was, like, a wonderful shock.

2631
01:47:05,900 --> 01:47:19,220
I went—when I went back to Athos in—so, one of the things Mary said to me at the end of the experience in Paris in 1998, I neglected to mention it the first iteration, she said, we will meet again, like a reassurance, we will meet again.

2632
01:47:20,600 --> 01:47:25,040
So, I said, oh, this is so great, you know, because this is like—this is the highlight of my life kind of thing.

2633
01:47:25,040 --> 01:47:32,120
And part of that would be, come back and visit me at Mount Athos again, where it all started.

2634
01:47:33,020 --> 01:47:38,380
So, it took me a long time between 1998, took me about seven years to go back.

2635
01:47:38,720 --> 01:47:39,420
I said, what, seven years?

2636
01:47:39,460 --> 01:47:39,900
Isn't that interesting?

2637
01:47:40,140 --> 01:47:46,720
And I went back to Mount Athos, and back at the Holy Mountain, only because I felt the Virgin Mary would now be my tour guide.

2638
01:47:47,440 --> 01:47:49,160
So, I did something kind of extraordinary.

2639
01:47:49,440 --> 01:47:50,840
I got the Greeks to allow me.

2640
01:47:50,840 --> 01:47:54,780
I knew the—I was still, like, with CIA, like, associated with CIA.

2641
01:47:54,780 --> 01:47:58,540
I was at the Department of Energy at that time, by the way, head of intelligence there.

2642
01:47:58,620 --> 01:48:05,840
But I still had all my contacts and friends at CIA, including the guy who was head of our office in Athens, right?

2643
01:48:06,480 --> 01:48:08,340
And I lined it up with him.

2644
01:48:08,360 --> 01:48:13,200
He's a close friend of mine, and he's also, interestingly enough, a religious scholar as CIA officer.

2645
01:48:13,280 --> 01:48:15,120
But he lined me up with a month-long visa.

2646
01:48:16,120 --> 01:48:18,320
Now, normally, someone like me, I could only get three days.

2647
01:48:18,320 --> 01:48:20,320
And I'd gotten one, and I'd never get another one.

2648
01:48:20,320 --> 01:48:24,680
But he had his contacts, and he explained my past, and they were like, oh, this is good stuff.

2649
01:48:25,240 --> 01:48:26,280
And I got a month.

2650
01:48:26,600 --> 01:48:28,600
So, I knock on the door, carry us.

2651
01:48:28,680 --> 01:48:36,280
I feel like—I feel a little like Alice in Wonderland or something, and sort of my mentality, right?

2652
01:48:36,340 --> 01:48:39,780
I'm going back, and just like, I'm just going to soak it all in.

2653
01:48:40,240 --> 01:48:42,240
And I feel guided the whole time.

2654
01:48:42,600 --> 01:48:46,300
And unlike most people, I didn't have to register what monastery I went to, what nights.

2655
01:48:46,300 --> 01:48:49,420
I just go one of the 20 of the monastery, and they have a number of what they call skeets.

2656
01:48:50,420 --> 01:48:51,560
Skeets are like miners.

2657
01:48:51,680 --> 01:48:52,300
They're not considered monasteries.

2658
01:48:52,980 --> 01:48:57,580
There are one or two monks there, and they're safeguarding a specific tradition or history of monathos.

2659
01:48:58,020 --> 01:49:00,800
So, for example, it was one—and I wandered and ran into these things.

2660
01:49:01,020 --> 01:49:03,000
It's a huge peninsula if you look on the map.

2661
01:49:03,000 --> 01:49:13,200
But I was wandering around and running into these things like I was being guided, and I felt like I was, going from place to place, showing up unannounced, spending a night going off into the woods.

2662
01:49:13,700 --> 01:49:17,720
By the way, just as a hiker-adventurer, it's like one of the most wonderful places on the planet.

2663
01:49:18,680 --> 01:49:24,260
So, I end up at St. Anski, which is where St. Anski is named in honor of Mary's mother, Anne.

2664
01:49:24,680 --> 01:49:27,760
I didn't even know that historical fact at that time.

2665
01:49:28,180 --> 01:49:29,940
Now, later, I would—many things.

2666
01:49:30,000 --> 01:49:32,240
So, I got into biblical archaeology and lived in the Middle East.

2667
01:49:32,240 --> 01:49:33,560
I got into all of this stuff.

2668
01:49:33,740 --> 01:49:40,240
And just as an aside, I didn't just do biblical archaeology of meaning Christian.

2669
01:49:40,960 --> 01:49:44,420
I did Old Testament, Judaism, Islam.

2670
01:49:44,720 --> 01:49:46,620
Did you try to find certain relics of that?

2671
01:49:46,620 --> 01:49:53,520
Oh, I tried to find all kinds of—but anyway, at St. Anski, they claimed to have her bones, some of her bones or whatever.

2672
01:49:53,800 --> 01:49:55,840
So, I mean, I'm kind of fascinated with that stuff, too.

2673
01:49:56,260 --> 01:49:58,560
And then the next day, I take off from there.

2674
01:49:58,620 --> 01:50:00,160
I said, well, I've been introduced to Mary's mother.

2675
01:50:00,220 --> 01:50:01,460
That would be something she would want.

2676
01:50:01,460 --> 01:50:04,480
And so, I take off from there, and I go down the coastline.

2677
01:50:04,560 --> 01:50:09,820
I catch a boat, go around the corner, the horn of Mon Althos.

2678
01:50:10,140 --> 01:50:16,560
And I end up at this bottom of this pier with a big walk up the side of a mountain.

2679
01:50:17,220 --> 01:50:18,840
And coincidence, right?

2680
01:50:19,280 --> 01:50:23,300
Coincidence is this monk walks by with a donkey who's going to go up there.

2681
01:50:23,640 --> 01:50:25,620
Little monk, and I've got my big backpack.

2682
01:50:25,620 --> 01:50:30,560
And so, come there a month, I've got a big backpack, one backpack for the month, but that's, you know, I've got everything in it.

2683
01:50:31,020 --> 01:50:33,660
And he goes, hey, why don't you take my donkey to the top of the mountain?

2684
01:50:33,880 --> 01:50:36,480
I said, this poor donkey, you sure you want to do it?

2685
01:50:36,520 --> 01:50:37,440
He goes, oh, he's used to it.

2686
01:50:37,520 --> 01:50:40,960
So, the guy just slaps him in the rear, and off we go.

2687
01:50:40,960 --> 01:50:46,160
And I'm sitting straddling this donkey up this cliff, afraid, like, I wouldn't want to let the monk down.

2688
01:50:46,240 --> 01:50:50,540
I was afraid I was going to go off the side and off into a cliff, an abyss, you know.

2689
01:50:50,900 --> 01:50:51,800
It's that kind of a thing.

2690
01:50:51,840 --> 01:50:56,360
And then it starts raining, and it's getting very steady donkey just up the mountain.

2691
01:50:56,760 --> 01:50:57,760
Get to the top of the mountain.

2692
01:50:57,840 --> 01:50:58,520
There's nobody there.

2693
01:50:58,600 --> 01:50:59,320
There are no pilgrims.

2694
01:50:59,380 --> 01:50:59,920
There's nobody there.

2695
01:50:59,960 --> 01:51:02,480
I walk into the entrance of the skeet.

2696
01:51:02,480 --> 01:51:07,400
And this guy comes out, greets me, a young monk, probably, you know, in the 30s.

2697
01:51:07,740 --> 01:51:09,180
He's the guy, caretaker there.

2698
01:51:09,200 --> 01:51:10,920
And he goes, well, let me tell you this history of this skeet.

2699
01:51:11,020 --> 01:51:17,800
It's called the Skeet Kaflosovakia, Kasasovakia.

2700
01:51:19,020 --> 01:51:20,180
I said, well, that's hard to say.

2701
01:51:20,240 --> 01:51:20,820
It's a mouthful.

2702
01:51:20,880 --> 01:51:26,900
He goes, yeah, this is named in the honor of one of the saints we have here, Saint Kaflosovakia,

2703
01:51:26,900 --> 01:51:28,560
who was known as Maximus the Monk.

2704
01:51:28,560 --> 01:51:30,120
He was not odious, Maximus.

2705
01:51:30,120 --> 01:51:35,800
And he was known as a flying monk, and he burned his huts, and he had these miracles,

2706
01:51:36,100 --> 01:51:37,900
and they were sightings of him flying.

2707
01:51:38,780 --> 01:51:39,640
I almost lost.

2708
01:51:39,780 --> 01:51:48,780
I mean, not lost is not the right expression, but I had a gasping for air just at the thought.

2709
01:51:49,960 --> 01:51:51,200
I hadn't made this up.

2710
01:51:52,080 --> 01:51:52,620
So crazy.

2711
01:51:52,760 --> 01:51:55,940
This had a historical connection, and I was there.

2712
01:51:56,600 --> 01:52:00,100
Normally, you could go a month at a month off, because you never run into this place.

2713
01:52:00,860 --> 01:52:03,940
But here I was, standing right at the front door, so to speak.

2714
01:52:04,040 --> 01:52:06,320
Well, you were meant to have that running.

2715
01:52:06,500 --> 01:52:08,560
Well, by now, I'm not doubting things like that.

2716
01:52:08,600 --> 01:52:12,780
You can take, by the way, I don't want people to go now think everything that happens to them is not by chance.

2717
01:52:13,220 --> 01:52:16,680
But you also have to be attuned to the possibility things aren't coincidence.

2718
01:52:17,060 --> 01:52:18,880
It's not believing everything is not a coincidence.

2719
01:52:18,880 --> 01:52:24,740
It's getting the right—being able to make a right judgment of when things aren't just coincidence.

2720
01:52:25,100 --> 01:52:32,980
Yeah, I think discernment is viewing patterns and synchronicities as possibly very meaningful and being attuned to them,

2721
01:52:33,040 --> 01:52:36,040
but not always taking them at face value.

2722
01:52:36,040 --> 01:52:47,840
But, I mean, yeah, you could literally right now Google Maximus Katsikovia, and this is this flying monk from Mount Athos,

2723
01:52:47,980 --> 01:52:50,220
and he was known for burning his huts.

2724
01:52:50,340 --> 01:52:55,880
And so it is fascinating that you went back in time not having any—you had no context.

2725
01:52:56,100 --> 01:52:56,700
No idea.

2726
01:52:56,700 --> 01:53:04,480
And then you find real historical corroboration for this through happenstance, and this is just online.

2727
01:53:04,620 --> 01:53:06,800
Like, people can search this open source.

2728
01:53:07,000 --> 01:53:09,060
That's pretty remarkable and interesting.

2729
01:53:10,140 --> 01:53:13,380
Do you think this was—you know, people talk about, like, past life regressions.

2730
01:53:13,920 --> 01:53:16,700
Do you think this was, like, a past life for you?

2731
01:53:16,940 --> 01:53:19,480
Well, I haven't really thought of that.

2732
01:53:19,480 --> 01:53:27,760
I don't think of—I don't say—I don't believe in reincarnation, but nor do I reject it.

2733
01:53:27,860 --> 01:53:29,160
I just—I mean, I don't know.

2734
01:53:29,280 --> 01:53:41,680
I don't have—I do have a fairly strong discipline in submitting everything we've talked about to a high degree of scrutiny,

2735
01:53:41,680 --> 01:53:50,660
to the point where—and you and I have talked about this—where sometimes I'm reticent to say the full—to provide the full effect of what I think I've learned or what I experienced,

2736
01:53:50,740 --> 01:54:01,260
because I don't—I don't want to—the one thing I can't do is misstate any of this, because that judgment comes down on me from God.

2737
01:54:01,380 --> 01:54:01,680
Yeah.

2738
01:54:01,920 --> 01:54:02,600
And God knows.

2739
01:54:02,600 --> 01:54:15,340
So you go through all this trouble to tell a story about your devotion to God and how you fulfill your destiny as being to fulfill God's will and do the right thing and do right by people, which is what it all boils down to, really does.

2740
01:54:16,620 --> 01:54:18,180
I can't misspeak on that.

2741
01:54:18,480 --> 01:54:22,140
You know, so I'm not going to inflate or add to an experience.

2742
01:54:22,220 --> 01:54:24,480
So the idea of, like, I love exploring with you.

2743
01:54:24,580 --> 01:54:26,880
I'm just being careful for your listeners and others.

2744
01:54:27,980 --> 01:54:30,140
We could talk about that over a beer or something.

2745
01:54:30,260 --> 01:54:31,440
I'd go way farther.

2746
01:54:31,440 --> 01:54:32,540
I don't know.

2747
01:54:32,680 --> 01:54:43,320
I think there's evidence out there that's like all the things, all the phenomena you research, Jesse, it should all be researched.

2748
01:54:43,840 --> 01:54:58,020
We should be very chery of drawing conclusions to things that are—that we don't have really solid evidence for, but nor should we be so respectful of conventional wisdom and science that we don't explore it.

2749
01:54:58,020 --> 01:55:01,260
And you should also give yourself the grace to speculate.

2750
01:55:01,260 --> 01:55:11,060
A, you know, everybody has a game of telephone they're playing in their mind where they don't remember anything accurately that's ever happened to them one-to-one perfectly.

2751
01:55:11,060 --> 01:55:14,680
But also the ability to speculate, which I know you do.

2752
01:55:14,680 --> 01:55:15,920
Oh, I do, I do.

2753
01:55:16,020 --> 01:55:28,120
And the thing about these experiences that I've described is that they do form a pattern, and the pattern becomes a major part of their authentication, you know, as being genuine.

2754
01:55:28,120 --> 01:55:36,480
And truth-related things, not truth-seeking, rather than self-focused or self-fulfilling.

2755
01:55:36,480 --> 01:55:59,040
I think part of the dreams at Monathos that I experienced was a necessary part of my own faith-based development that I would—the more you discuss or try to convey a belief in God, the more you have to remove yourself as the object of your intentions.

2756
01:55:59,580 --> 01:56:02,160
This is one of the most important things I can say.

2757
01:56:02,160 --> 01:56:14,840
If you're, you know, one of the apostles who followed—and I'm not, I'm not putting myself on any level with the people I'll describe—you have to be willing to be a martyr to pull that truth forward and become part of human history.

2758
01:56:14,840 --> 01:56:24,360
Because God needed, Christ needed them to go out, as they did all over the world, in the way they did.

2759
01:56:24,440 --> 01:56:30,400
And they needed, in a way, one of the proofs they were willing to do is lay down their own lives for the truth.

2760
01:56:30,860 --> 01:56:36,160
And it's easy to say, lay down your life for the truth, but, you know, it's a harder thing to do it.

2761
01:56:36,420 --> 01:56:38,620
And the other thing is to not do it for their own benefit.

2762
01:56:38,620 --> 01:56:43,040
Because you can even lay your life down for the truth because you think it's to your benefit, but it's not even your goal.

2763
01:56:43,760 --> 01:56:45,600
At some point, you try to eliminate yourself.

2764
01:56:46,020 --> 01:57:00,980
The object of—the paragraphs I wrote of my time at Monathos in my dream, I tried to be very, very careful to describe the essence of what I was experiencing in the dream, which was this process of shedding myself.

2765
01:57:00,980 --> 01:57:07,280
It's the reason, when I read Meister Eckhart or somebody like that, he talks about looking down at God, not up.

2766
01:57:07,780 --> 01:57:11,480
It's a psychological thing, you know, ashes to ashes, dust to dust.

2767
01:57:11,780 --> 01:57:22,540
The more you can remove yourself from any honor or glory in faith, the closer—the more responsibility God will give you, if that makes sense, to promote the faith.

2768
01:57:22,920 --> 01:57:24,540
Because it can't be about you.

2769
01:57:24,540 --> 01:57:27,600
And there's a—yeah, well said.

2770
01:57:27,700 --> 01:57:34,540
There's a Yale professor, who's very well-respected, a religious studies professor named Carlos Ayer.

2771
01:57:35,080 --> 01:57:40,060
He wrote a book called They Flew, and it's all about flying saints and monks.

2772
01:57:40,900 --> 01:57:46,760
And St. Joseph the Divine, St. Joseph of Cupertino, is probably the most famous example.

2773
01:57:46,880 --> 01:57:48,040
I think he was 16th century.

2774
01:57:48,040 --> 01:57:55,100
You have Teresa Avila, who also seemed to experience, you know, bilocation and all these sort of other paranormal things.

2775
01:57:55,180 --> 01:57:58,040
Even St. Francis of Assisi, by some accounts, might have levitated.

2776
01:57:59,880 --> 01:58:09,860
And so this is actually—and this guy went into this research thinking, oh, you know, this must have been written about sort of historically in this sort of metaphorical way.

2777
01:58:09,860 --> 01:58:19,420
And he came out of it being like, no, there's enough eyewitness testimony around these flying saints to call it history.

2778
01:58:19,700 --> 01:58:25,280
And it's well beyond the threshold of evidence we'd need to say that, like, the War of 1812 was fought or whatever.

2779
01:58:26,240 --> 01:58:28,300
And I think he truly believes that.

2780
01:58:28,460 --> 01:58:33,040
And, you know, I have a friend named Diana Pasulka who's a religious studies professor at UNC Wilmington.

2781
01:58:33,040 --> 01:58:42,000
And she's gone very deep on St. Joseph of Cupertino, and she has gone through a lot of his files, and she agrees with that.

2782
01:58:42,400 --> 01:58:46,000
So—and it's across, like you said, it's across different religions.

2783
01:58:46,220 --> 01:58:54,780
So maybe this is a real phenomenon where you do shed the baggage of individual ego, and you become one with God, and you fly.

2784
01:58:54,780 --> 01:59:06,320
There's even, in fact, Jeffrey Kripal, who's a religious studies professor at Rice University in Houston, he was giving a lecture on flying saints at MIT.

2785
01:59:06,660 --> 01:59:07,080
Oh, wow.

2786
01:59:07,080 --> 01:59:21,140
And a guy who I've met, actually, who runs revolutionary technologies at Skunk Works, their most advanced R&D division, obviously, of Lockheed Martin, and he's running their most advanced R&D division of Skunk Works.

2787
01:59:22,160 --> 01:59:26,780
He attended the lecture and was very interested in flying saints.

2788
01:59:27,320 --> 01:59:27,780
That's so great.

2789
01:59:27,880 --> 01:59:28,620
It's interesting.

2790
01:59:28,860 --> 01:59:29,240
That's so great.

2791
01:59:29,300 --> 01:59:29,620
Yeah.

2792
01:59:29,620 --> 01:59:40,880
Well, I don't think there's any question that once you start believing in certain mystical experiences, either because you've experienced them yourselves or you've heard such compelling tales.

2793
01:59:40,980 --> 01:59:56,880
Like, I read Virgin Mary, which I didn't know, as I stress a lot, really the history of those appearances until now, of course, I sort of study them to look at the similarities, to hear the different descriptions, see how close they were to mine.

2794
01:59:56,880 --> 02:00:02,180
And then what's very reassuring is I see sort of so many similarities and commonalities.

2795
02:00:02,600 --> 02:00:17,860
But the point is, to your explanation, yeah, you've got to be willing to believe all kinds of manifestations, what I would call the holy, meaning things that are not of human construction, whether it's our minds or even what we call the laws of physics.

2796
02:00:18,000 --> 02:00:19,480
They come from something else.

2797
02:00:19,820 --> 02:00:22,280
What's the physics of that or where is that?

2798
02:00:22,280 --> 02:00:28,600
The where might even be, you know, not a real question because it may not be anywhere in that sense.

2799
02:00:28,680 --> 02:00:30,520
We understand location, right?

2800
02:00:30,720 --> 02:00:36,340
Because what's location outside of distance and motion and it's really nothing, right?

2801
02:00:36,640 --> 02:00:38,280
So is it over, under, or aside?

2802
02:00:38,380 --> 02:00:39,700
I'm sure it's relevant.

2803
02:00:39,900 --> 02:00:41,920
But then you're getting closer to all the mystics.

2804
02:00:41,920 --> 02:00:57,080
Because when they get together, I've read, you know, some really cool stuff and I'd love to be in one of those gatherings when Merton used to have them in Asia and you had Buddhist mystics and you had Islamic mystics and poets.

2805
02:00:57,520 --> 02:01:00,420
Hafiz, for example, one of my favorite, talking about his love of God.

2806
02:01:00,420 --> 02:01:10,320
And the heretics who were burned and things for going too far with things that were mystical, they couldn't help themselves because they were just devoted to the truth.

2807
02:01:10,860 --> 02:01:19,360
Their crime is always, which is why Elijah was sought in half, or is speaking truth to people who don't want to hear it.

2808
02:01:19,360 --> 02:01:30,180
Or sounding enigmatic because their prophecies or what they see in the future don't accord with the conventional wisdom of the day.

2809
02:01:31,860 --> 02:01:33,420
That's usually the problem.

2810
02:01:33,820 --> 02:01:46,060
Is there some version of that you think you have, some truth that from all of these mystical experiences you've come back with that the average person might have kind of an allergic reaction to or might not want to hear, might be an uncomfortable truth?

2811
02:01:46,060 --> 02:01:50,340
Well, I think, I think, frankly, an average person is probably uncomfortable with all of this.

2812
02:01:50,460 --> 02:01:50,780
Yeah.

2813
02:01:51,040 --> 02:01:51,300
Right?

2814
02:01:51,400 --> 02:01:52,560
I mean, let's be honest, right?

2815
02:01:52,620 --> 02:01:54,620
And it's the idea, well, who do you think you are?

2816
02:01:54,640 --> 02:01:55,880
It starts with things like that.

2817
02:01:56,400 --> 02:02:11,220
And it's, the mistake, of course, is over, over-interpretation or look, because I've realized also, this is just something I've learned, because I continue to occasionally have enigmatic dreams.

2818
02:02:11,220 --> 02:02:28,060
I don't mean anything as vivid as in the past, in fact, with age, it's less, fewer and fewer, which I, when I was living in the Middle East, I once went to my Jesuit priest friend, friend more than any, more than a spiritual advisor, and said, you know, I just don't know what my purpose is anymore now that I'm not meeting the Virgin Mary.

2819
02:02:28,240 --> 02:02:31,900
I said, I don't want to sound, you know, like I should be meeting Virgin Mary, but I sure miss it.

2820
02:02:31,900 --> 02:02:34,960
And he goes, well, have you tried praying to her?

2821
02:02:35,020 --> 02:02:37,020
I said, well, I don't really pray to the Virgin Mary.

2822
02:02:37,420 --> 02:02:39,000
I feel her presence.

2823
02:02:39,840 --> 02:02:42,060
But I pray to God, and I pray to, you know, Jesus Christ.

2824
02:02:42,140 --> 02:02:42,440
That's it.

2825
02:02:42,460 --> 02:02:43,920
I don't pray to other people or other things.

2826
02:02:44,080 --> 02:02:47,620
But he said, well, you can pray, but just don't get hung up on the word.

2827
02:02:47,720 --> 02:02:48,480
You can interact.

2828
02:02:48,560 --> 02:02:49,160
You can talk.

2829
02:02:49,880 --> 02:02:57,300
And so I asked, I said, well, you know, Mary, what's my, why am I here?

2830
02:02:57,840 --> 02:02:58,900
Like, why am I in the Middle East?

2831
02:02:58,900 --> 02:03:06,280
I have the sense I was praying or thinking that there's a reason I'm here, and that you brought me here, because why would we be here?

2832
02:03:07,200 --> 02:03:14,160
And I was spending all my time in five years in the Middle East, 2011 to 16, spending all my time on the road.

2833
02:03:14,600 --> 02:03:16,260
I did biblical archaeology.

2834
02:03:17,180 --> 02:03:18,640
I did, you know, went on tour.

2835
02:03:18,680 --> 02:03:20,960
I went all over everywhere many times over.

2836
02:03:21,100 --> 02:03:23,600
Then later on, you know, in Saudi Arabia, et cetera.

2837
02:03:24,080 --> 02:03:25,660
And I said, there's got to be a reason for this.

2838
02:03:25,660 --> 02:03:29,360
So I used to say, just, just tell me so I know what I should expect kind of thing.

2839
02:03:29,940 --> 02:03:38,060
And got back kind of a, again, nothing verbal or just an answer, which was, you're here to be here.

2840
02:03:39,680 --> 02:03:41,040
And it put me at ease.

2841
02:03:41,180 --> 02:03:45,240
It was the idea, okay, this is almost like, I don't need to overthink this.

2842
02:03:45,240 --> 02:03:50,980
I think in other messages, she says, don't, to you, don't strive, don't try, don't reach.

2843
02:03:51,820 --> 02:04:00,940
This was in, well, 1998 was when I, seven years after I met her at Mount Athos, I met her in Paris, met the Virgin Mary.

2844
02:04:01,480 --> 02:04:07,680
So that, none of this discussion would be occurring if I hadn't actually met the Virgin Mary.

2845
02:04:07,680 --> 02:04:10,840
And we call it the apparition, and I mean the Virgin Mary.

2846
02:04:11,040 --> 02:04:14,880
So I had a, was in Paris on a work trip for CIA.

2847
02:04:15,980 --> 02:04:18,540
I was doing actually Russian things.

2848
02:04:18,640 --> 02:04:23,300
I was heading up a lot of our Russian, CIA's Russian activity at the time, 1998.

2849
02:04:23,940 --> 02:04:27,640
And so I'm in Paris for those discussions with one other colleague.

2850
02:04:27,640 --> 02:04:36,220
And he, we both went, you know, we, we, we signed up at a big boutique hotel, five minute walk from Arc de Triomphe kind of, you know, place.

2851
02:04:36,420 --> 02:04:44,260
And no, not from Arc de Triomphe, from, from the American embassy down in the southern part of the, that lane, Arc de Triomphe down there, Hotel Crayon area.

2852
02:04:44,920 --> 02:04:46,780
And we're in the, I'm in the hotel.

2853
02:04:47,040 --> 02:04:48,380
It's a nice little room.

2854
02:04:48,380 --> 02:04:53,640
And it had a bed with a old fashioned hotel, really old.

2855
02:04:53,920 --> 02:04:59,940
And it had a table in front of me and had a light switch on the wall, but small room, typical French style.

2856
02:05:00,720 --> 02:05:10,980
And as I went to bed, thinking nothing in particular, except maybe my last thoughts before going to sleep was going through my notes in my mind of what we were going to raise the next day.

2857
02:05:10,980 --> 02:05:22,140
And, uh, as I like to joke, I didn't have any weird food or anything else and went to sleep and immediately was there, like in one of those dreams again.

2858
02:05:23,640 --> 02:05:25,960
And I knew it right away, but it was a dream.

2859
02:05:26,160 --> 02:05:26,840
I knew I was dreaming.

2860
02:05:27,240 --> 02:05:28,640
So I'm by a river bank.

2861
02:05:28,700 --> 02:05:32,060
So I'm thinking of the river dream from way back, which was a more raging river.

2862
02:05:32,140 --> 02:05:36,540
This is a nice, gentle, almost stream type river.

2863
02:05:36,540 --> 02:05:40,000
And I'm sitting at a river bank of grass, lush grass.

2864
02:05:40,140 --> 02:05:41,040
It's a beautiful day.

2865
02:05:41,800 --> 02:05:43,040
Again, balmy, nice weather.

2866
02:05:43,140 --> 02:05:51,040
I'm sitting on the top of the little, little mound that goes in, goes down into the stream and there's nobody around.

2867
02:05:51,280 --> 02:05:53,560
And I'm just thinking, just relaxing.

2868
02:05:53,860 --> 02:06:05,280
And then an old woman comes dressed in a brown, uh, brown cloak with a hood up and sits almost within touching distance, but just outside my reach.

2869
02:06:05,280 --> 02:06:09,540
And sits there and stares, looks ahead too.

2870
02:06:09,760 --> 02:06:11,200
And I didn't want to disturb her.

2871
02:06:11,260 --> 02:06:13,160
So I didn't like introduce myself or say anything.

2872
02:06:13,200 --> 02:06:16,820
I just thought, uh, maybe wait for her to say hi or something.

2873
02:06:16,880 --> 02:06:17,580
I won't do it.

2874
02:06:17,820 --> 02:06:21,440
And so we're just sitting there and then it starts sprinkling.

2875
02:06:22,900 --> 02:06:24,460
And it was, the sun stayed up.

2876
02:06:24,540 --> 02:06:25,600
The sun didn't go away.

2877
02:06:25,660 --> 02:06:28,340
So I thought it was just a little sprinkle when the sun's out.

2878
02:06:28,340 --> 02:06:32,860
And it's, as it's hitting my skin, I remember hitting my arm and hands first.

2879
02:06:33,480 --> 02:06:36,000
I see brown, like oozing brown dirt.

2880
02:06:37,840 --> 02:06:41,760
And I thought, wow, this is really kind of strange.

2881
02:06:42,280 --> 02:06:47,380
And then I looked to see what reaction the woman was having to this strange rain.

2882
02:06:47,380 --> 02:07:02,880
And, and I, at that time she, when turned towards me and I felt this kind of ease, I felt really at ease and I felt kind of backwards, like almost like, whoa, into her arms.

2883
02:07:02,880 --> 02:07:06,860
And then I realized it was a Virgin Mary.

2884
02:07:07,720 --> 02:07:11,400
And I thought at that moment, I thought, okay, it's a dream.

2885
02:07:12,400 --> 02:07:17,740
Um, and I think this rain is like, I don't know, purifying me or something.

2886
02:07:18,280 --> 02:07:19,740
I just had that weird thought.

2887
02:07:19,880 --> 02:07:27,120
So then I wake up, so I wake up in my room and I get up to turn on the light because I need to clear my head.

2888
02:07:27,260 --> 02:07:29,060
You know, it was very jarring.

2889
02:07:29,180 --> 02:07:31,300
It was very jarring in a nice way, but very jarring.

2890
02:07:31,300 --> 02:07:33,520
How did you know it was the Virgin Mary in the dream?

2891
02:07:33,720 --> 02:07:34,520
I just knew it then.

2892
02:07:34,640 --> 02:07:35,040
You just knew it.

2893
02:07:35,040 --> 02:07:36,160
I just knew that was the Virgin Mary.

2894
02:07:36,160 --> 02:07:36,460
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

2895
02:07:36,460 --> 02:07:37,900
Unlike the other things I said.

2896
02:07:37,900 --> 02:07:38,600
Where you weren't as sure.

2897
02:07:38,960 --> 02:07:40,200
Where I wasn't as sure.

2898
02:07:40,520 --> 02:07:42,340
This, I knew right away, this was a Virgin Mary.

2899
02:07:42,580 --> 02:07:49,740
Because I had had the one experience too in Portugal where I met the Virgin Mary, but not in the flesh and in the mind kind of thing.

2900
02:07:49,820 --> 02:07:51,780
So this was like completely normal to me now.

2901
02:07:52,880 --> 02:07:54,520
The dream, that I would have a dream like this.

2902
02:07:54,580 --> 02:07:57,840
It was not no longer some, maybe what all this was, was preparation, right?

2903
02:07:57,840 --> 02:08:02,020
Because all along the way, I was getting more and more used to the idea that this wasn't strange.

2904
02:08:03,160 --> 02:08:04,280
None of this was strange.

2905
02:08:04,360 --> 02:08:07,640
This was all part of a sort of a process in a way.

2906
02:08:08,100 --> 02:08:11,760
So I get up on the, from the chair, I hit my shin.

2907
02:08:11,900 --> 02:08:15,480
I forget, I hurt my shin bone as I got up.

2908
02:08:15,500 --> 02:08:17,360
And that's how I kind of knew I was awake.

2909
02:08:17,360 --> 02:08:20,740
And then I saw this, like, like we're sitting in a room here.

2910
02:08:20,740 --> 02:08:25,320
It was in that corner coming from the top of the corner, a light coming down like this.

2911
02:08:26,480 --> 02:08:27,240
Radiant light.

2912
02:08:27,620 --> 02:08:33,180
And Thomas Merton described the light better than I could when I read it in one of his books.

2913
02:08:33,780 --> 02:08:35,580
Because he had some of these experiences.

2914
02:08:35,780 --> 02:08:40,780
It was a light so bright that it bore no resemblance to visible light.

2915
02:08:41,340 --> 02:08:42,480
If that makes sense.

2916
02:08:42,480 --> 02:08:47,360
So it didn't shy, you'd have to look away from it, it was very bright.

2917
02:08:47,880 --> 02:08:52,000
And it came and sat straight in front of me when I was standing up.

2918
02:08:52,040 --> 02:08:56,920
I was still standing up where the curtains are, like right across from me when I'm standing there.

2919
02:08:57,220 --> 02:09:04,420
And off the ground was the full image of the Virgin Mary.

2920
02:09:04,560 --> 02:09:04,880
Wow.

2921
02:09:05,340 --> 02:09:06,240
In your room?

2922
02:09:06,400 --> 02:09:06,940
In my room.

2923
02:09:07,940 --> 02:09:08,240
Wow.

2924
02:09:08,240 --> 02:09:10,880
So she was in the dream and then she comes into your room?

2925
02:09:10,880 --> 02:09:21,400
And I knew, as I was standing there, I specifically had the realization, clear, absolute realization, this is not a dream.

2926
02:09:21,500 --> 02:09:22,740
In fact, I kind of pinched myself.

2927
02:09:23,140 --> 02:09:27,020
This is reality as opposed to, and the dream must be preparation.

2928
02:09:28,080 --> 02:09:29,200
What happens next?

2929
02:09:29,240 --> 02:09:30,000
So she's in your room.

2930
02:09:30,040 --> 02:09:36,100
She's in my room and then I don't have any conversations, but I can read her mind or she can read my mind or vice versa.

2931
02:09:36,460 --> 02:09:37,680
There's an exchange.

2932
02:09:37,680 --> 02:09:44,480
There's communication going on at a nonverbal level and it's very intense.

2933
02:09:44,480 --> 02:10:05,160
I'm feeling combination, you know, at the one time a rushing sense of grief that she's feeling at the same time, the hope of the message she's conveying that in the end it will all come out fine, but there's this tremendous pain and suffering.

2934
02:10:05,160 --> 02:10:11,940
And she said it when, like, said, I knew the message clearly, got the message, write a letter to the Pope.

2935
02:10:12,480 --> 02:10:20,020
No instructions what to write or what you've seen, seeing me, but no other specific instructions what to say or why.

2936
02:10:20,260 --> 02:10:22,260
No explanation, but just write a letter to the Pope.

2937
02:10:22,260 --> 02:10:31,060
Then I was looking for some form of greater understanding, I'd say, and she sensed that.

2938
02:10:31,920 --> 02:10:35,820
And I think she sensed I was, like, still shocked, in shock, right?

2939
02:10:36,060 --> 02:10:41,080
But I went into a state of ecstasy.

2940
02:10:41,080 --> 02:10:44,140
So I've never had that.

2941
02:10:45,420 --> 02:10:50,340
Only time in my life, 71 years old, that I was in a state of ecstasy.

2942
02:10:51,840 --> 02:10:54,900
I could, I remember my teeth chattering.

2943
02:10:56,300 --> 02:10:57,160
I remember that.

2944
02:10:57,260 --> 02:11:01,660
I remember the sound of them going, and my head going back, like, it was like, and it was incredible.

2945
02:11:01,660 --> 02:11:09,440
It was like an incredible orgasm of, like, beyond that, without a real orgasm, obviously.

2946
02:11:09,520 --> 02:11:12,700
But it was, like, more than, it was just an incredible feeling.

2947
02:11:13,660 --> 02:11:16,360
The bona fides of the moment, so to speak, were right there.

2948
02:11:16,480 --> 02:11:19,500
I mean, this is absolutely what it was.

2949
02:11:19,540 --> 02:11:27,980
And then I saw it, like, more of a, if I'm so graced to be here in your presence, you know, I've sent, you know,

2950
02:11:27,980 --> 02:11:35,640
then there must be something specific you want me to do, other than the letter to the Pope, and that sort of thing.

2951
02:11:35,740 --> 02:11:41,080
And then little things came out, like, for example, a sense of tying together.

2952
02:11:41,680 --> 02:11:44,720
There was no numbers, but I sensed that it was all related.

2953
02:11:44,920 --> 02:11:47,720
I just sensed that it was all related to this.

2954
02:11:47,720 --> 02:11:53,820
Plus, my encounter I'd had with her in Portugal, where I hadn't met her, but I felt her mind and thoughts.

2955
02:11:53,820 --> 02:12:00,520
She was explaining when she told me there, deliver the message, write what you see.

2956
02:12:02,420 --> 02:12:04,300
Whatever you do, you do in sin.

2957
02:12:05,000 --> 02:12:05,700
That was specific.

2958
02:12:05,740 --> 02:12:09,480
I wrote that down after Portugal, which was a few years earlier.

2959
02:12:09,800 --> 02:12:15,000
Said, keep all that in mind as you go forth on this mission, or you go forth to fulfill God's will.

2960
02:12:15,160 --> 02:12:17,560
And she made it clear everything is God's will, not her will.

2961
02:12:17,780 --> 02:12:19,440
There was a major distinction.

2962
02:12:19,740 --> 02:12:21,180
I wasn't doing anything for her.

2963
02:12:21,180 --> 02:12:28,960
However, this was all in accordance with her serving God, the same way she was asking me to, or anybody else.

2964
02:12:30,080 --> 02:12:37,980
Now, you asked earlier, at this point, I had never read anything about her encounters with the Virgin Mary.

2965
02:12:38,040 --> 02:12:41,720
But I became, of course, a student of that as well, great detail.

2966
02:12:41,720 --> 02:12:53,160
But the thing that you mentioned earlier, I think she sensed that I was, not losing it, but needed further reassurance in some way that I could do this.

2967
02:12:53,200 --> 02:13:01,680
Because the first thing anybody has is an expectation of getting any mystical experience that's genuine is, well, why me?

2968
02:13:01,680 --> 02:13:05,900
There's no reason, the answer to that is, there is no reason, it's you.

2969
02:13:07,100 --> 02:13:11,280
I wasn't being singled out because I was noble, or worthy, or no such reason.

2970
02:13:12,080 --> 02:13:20,740
When Paul was on the road to Damascus and he was struck down by the light of Jesus standing over him, the light, the divine light of Jesus saying,

2971
02:13:20,740 --> 02:13:33,540
Paul, why are you persecuting me, he turns from a person going to kill members of this Jewish sect to the leader of that sect because of the mystical experience with Christ.

2972
02:13:33,720 --> 02:13:35,360
Without that, none of that would have happened.

2973
02:13:35,360 --> 02:13:48,700
And so, you know, I'm very well aware that these aren't only real, but they're incredible, important moments in human history every time they happen to anybody to continue to gather them up.

2974
02:13:48,700 --> 02:13:51,540
And as you're saying, tell, relate the story.

2975
02:13:51,720 --> 02:13:57,780
So at the very end of the encounter, it was, you know, it's funny, time kind of like, I got lost in time.

